 The idea of an apostacy did not originate with Lucy Smith or Joseph Smith or the Mormons.  The idea of a restoration was quite common in the early 19th century USA.  Alexander Campbell founder of the group that now survives with the name Disciples of Christ preached that the primitive church had been lost and was attempting to restore it (although not be revelations).  Many Cambellites subsequently became Mormons including co-founder Sidney Rigdon.  Actually you can find such sentiments in many of the early protestants of the reformation such as Martin Luther. --  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- Gordon Banks  N3JXP      | Skepticism is the chastity of the intellect
