use the parent has told the child that it is wrong. Now the parent may swear like a trooper in the pub or bar (where there are no children). The wrongness here is if the child disobeys the parent. The parent may feel that it is inappropriate to swear in front of children but may be quite happy to swear in front of animals. The analogy does not quite hold water because the child knows that he is of the same type as the parent (and may be a parent later in life) but you get the gist of it? Incidentally

