 \tI\m not sure that you can distinguish between myth and legend so neatly or at all.  A myth is more than a single story.  The thought  structure and world-paradigm in which that story is interpreted is as important a part of the myth as the story itself.  Thus I can think of no story which is meant to be conveyed understandably from one person to another within a single culture which won\t rest upon that underlying thought structure
